-- England Selects Goode for Third Rugby Test Against South Africa
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-06-21T08:51:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/england-selects-goode-for-third-rugby-test-against-south-africa.html
England coach Stuart Lancaster made
six changes for the third rugby Test against South Africa in
Port Elizabeth, with Alex Goode set to make his first
international start at fullback.  No. 8 Thomas Waldrom will also start for a first time, with
Danny Care,  James Haskell , Alex Corbisiero and Tom Palmer
returning to the  lineup  for the June 23 match.  Ben Foden  moves
from fullback to the left wing.  South Africa has an unbeatable 2-0 lead in the three-match
series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Cone  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  